        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(usage): remove argsMenu: auto from /usage command to fix Telegram toggle",
        "body": "## Problem\n`/usage` command registered with `argsMenu: \"auto\"`, causing Telegram to misinterpret the command as having sub-commands and toggle behavior incorrectly. The `/usage full` variant supplies a `mode` argument, and `resolveCommandArgMenu` returns `null` when args are present, but bare `/usage` triggers the broken menu behavior.\n\nFixes #93905\n\n## Fix\nRemove `argsMenu: \"auto\"` from the built-in `/usage` command registration in `src/auto-reply/commands-registry.shared.ts`. The native command name (`usage`) and handler remain in place. The `/usage full` path with explicit mode argument still works correctly because it bypasses the menu.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Before (broken)\n- `/usage` registered with `argsMenu: \"auto\"` in `commands-registry.shared.ts`\n- Telegram client interprets the command as having sub-commands\n- Tapping `/usage` opens a sub-command toggle instead of executing the command directly\n\n### After (fixed)\n- `argsMenu` field removed from `/usage` registration\n- Telegram treats `/usage` as a simple command with no sub-menu\n- `/usage full` continues to work correctly with explicit `mode` argument\n\n### Reproduction\n1. Open a Telegram chat with the bot\n2. Type `/usage` — before fix: shows sub-command toggle; after fix: executes directly\n3. Type `/usage full` — works the same before and after\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n$ vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.auto-reply.config.ts src/auto-reply/commands-registry.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  31 passed (31)\n   Duration  7.71s\n```\n\nAll 31 command registry tests pass including command registration, argument parsing, and native menu resolution.",
